tions made about gender in Christine’s works. It also examines the conduits and structures by which power is conferred upon women within them. When read together, the text and image across Christine’s œuvre reveal a consistent picture: one in which women educate and empower one another.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminism in art. 0aFeminism in literature. 0aWomen in art. 0aWomen in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aChristine de Pizan.  agender.  amedieval France.  apower.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781802701494?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781802701494423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781802701494/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles